# ============================================================
# TRIGGRR — Environment Variables Template
# ============================================================
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file:   cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in the two values below
#   3. Restart the dev server:  npm run dev
#
# IMPORTANT:
#   .env is listed in .gitignore and will NOT be committed.
#   .env.example (this file) CAN be committed — it has no real keys.
#   On Vercel: add these as Environment Variables in the dashboard.
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Add
# ============================================================


# ─── Google Apps Script Web App URL ─────────────────────────
#
# This is the endpoint that receives Contact form submissions
# and writes them to your Google Sheet.
#
# How to get it:
#   1. Open your Google Sheet
#   2. Extensions → Apps Script
#   3. Paste GoogleAppsScript.gs (from this project)
#   4. Click Deploy → New Deployment
#   5. Type: Web App
#   6. Execute as: Me
#   7. Who has access: Anyone
#   8. Click Deploy → Authorise when prompted
#   9. Copy the Web App URL that appears
#
# The URL looks like:
#   https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycb.../exec
#
# NOTE: The URL changes only when you create a NEW deployment
#       (not when you redeploy an existing one with "new version").
#       Update Vercel env vars if you ever create a new deployment.
#
VITE_SCRIPT_URL=https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbylIfo1HeBcbDzakHyCNN0c0ntXuieNyzaNS1ahV7sEZr4jEzzIPVaKDjbPL5m3mv1MEw/exec


# ─── Google reCAPTCHA v3 Site Key ───────────────────────────
#
# Protects the contact form from bots.
# This is the PUBLIC site key — safe to expose in frontend code.
# (The SECRET key goes in GoogleAppsScript.gs CONFIG, not here.)
#
# How to get it:
#   1. Go to: https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create
#   2. Label: "Triggrr Contact Form"
#   3. reCAPTCHA type: v3
#   4. Domains: add your domain (e.g. triggrr.io)
#              also add: localhost (for local dev)
#   5. Click Submit → copy the SITE KEY (not the secret key)
#
# Leave blank during development if you haven't set it up yet.
# The Contact form degrades gracefully — submissions still work
# without reCAPTCHA, just without bot protection.
#
VITE_RECAPTCHA_KEY=6LfsFhktAAAAADHOiXso3jAAJBbjI2HE09l8aJ6Q
